    "This line operator is 2 valued: due to the first fusion rule, its square must be a line operator living on the world-volume of D (SC) 2, but the only such line operator is the identity one.Gauging the 2 1-form symmetry generated by D (V) 2 leads to the O(4N) theory.",
    "The surface operator furnishing the desired 2-charge is O 2 = D the image in the O(4N) theory of the operator D 1-form symmetry arising after the above gauging, which can be identified as the magnetic 1-form symmetry of the O(4N) theory.",
    "The line operator D (V; SC) 1 becomes a line operator living on the world-volume of D localized symmetry of it.",
    "Additionally, the generator D (V; SC) 1 of this localized symmetry has to be charged under the 2 1-form symmetry induced on O 2 by the bulk magnetic 1-form symmetry, because before the gauging the line operator D (V; SC) 1 lied at the end of the topological operator D (V) 2 being gauged.",
    "This means that we have a 't Hooft anomaly (96) and hence the proposed surface operator O 2 indeed furnishes the desired non-trivial 2-charge. 2.2of 3-charges."
